.TH ASRFACET-RB 1 "April 2026" "ASRFacet-Rb 1.5.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
asrfacet-rb \- authorized attack surface reconnaissance and security mapping framework
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B asrfacet-rb
<command> [arguments] [options]
.br
.B asrfacet-rb
--version
.br
.B asrfacet-rb
--console
.br
.B asrfacet-rb
--web-session
.br
.B asrfacet-rb
manual [section]
.br
.B man
asrfacet-rb
.br
.B man
asrfrb
.SH DESCRIPTION
ASRFacet-Rb is a Ruby 3.2+ framework for authorized attack surface reconnaissance.
It combines passive discovery, recursive DNS and certificate enrichment, service mapping,
HTTP probing, crawling, JavaScript endpoint mining, asset scoring, monitoring, and
lightweight finding generation.
.PP
The framework is intended only for systems you own or have explicit written permission
to test. Scope control, recon memory, and educational self-documentation are built in.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B scan DOMAIN
Run the full reconnaissance pipeline. Aliases: s, sc.
.TP
.B passive DOMAIN
Run passive discovery only. Aliases: p, pa.
.TP
.B ports HOST
Run a focused TCP port scan. Aliases: pt, po.
.TP
.B dns DOMAIN
Collect DNS records only. Aliases: d, dn.
.TP
.B console
Launch the framework console. Aliases: c, con, shell.
.TP
.B web
Launch the local web control panel. Aliases: w, ui.
.TP
.B interactive
Launch the standalone guided workflow. Aliases: i, int.
.TP
.B help [topic], explain TOPIC, manual [section]
Show built-in documentation. Help aliases: h, ?. Explain aliases: x, exp. Manual aliases: m, man. Version aliases: v, ver.
.SH CONSOLE
The console is the richest operator interface and supports framework-style commands such as:
.IP
show commands
.br
show options
.br
show workflow
.br
show config
.br
show learning
.br
info recon
.br
man
.br
wizard
.PP
Normal framework commands can also be run directly inside the console.
.SH WEB SESSION
Web session mode starts a local browser-facing control panel, bound to 127.0.0.1:4567
by default unless overridden.
It keeps saved sessions, live activity, report links, and built-in docs in one shell.
.PP
The web UI is local, not hosted. Drafts are stored under
.I ~/.asrfacet_rb/web_sessions/
and runs still use the same underlying reconnaissance pipeline as the CLI.
.SH WIZARD
The console-only wizard asks what you are trying to achieve, how careful you want to be,
what format you want, and whether monitoring or memory should be enabled.
It then recommends a concrete command and can execute it for you.
.SH RECON BASICS
Passive reconnaissance uses third-party data without touching the target.
Active reconnaissance confirms assets by making requests or opening connections.
Effective attack surface mapping combines both approaches, then ranks the results so
deeper testing focuses on the most valuable assets first.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Project defaults are stored in
.I config/default.yml
and user overrides are stored in
.I ~/.asrfacet_rb/config.yml .
Common settings include timeouts, thread counts, wordlists, output preferences, and HTTP behavior.
.SH OUTPUTS
.TP
.B cli
Terminal-friendly tables and summaries.
.TP
.B json
Machine-readable output.
.TP
.B html
Offline report with findings, graph relationships, and top targets.
.TP
.B txt
Plain-text export.
.PP
Automatic report bundles are stored under
.I ~/.asrfacet_rb/output/reports/<target>/<timestamp>/
and event streams may be written under
.I ~/.asrfacet_rb/output/streams/ .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I bin/asrfacet-rb
Primary executable.
.TP
.I bin/asrfrb
Short alias executable.
.TP
.I config/default.yml
Project defaults.
.TP
.I ~/.asrfacet_rb/config.yml
User configuration overrides.
.TP
.I ~/.asrfacet_rb/memory/
Per-target scan memory.
.TP
.I ~/.asrfacet_rb/output/
Stored reports and generated artifacts.
.TP
.I ~/.asrfacet_rb/web_sessions/
Persistent web-session drafts and recovered state.
.TP
.I man/asrfacet-rb.1
Primary manual page source.
.TP
.I man/asrfrb.1
Alias manual page source.
.SH TRANSPARENCY
Active modes make real DNS, TCP, HTTP, and related requests to the targets you configure.
Passive results are lead generation, not guaranteed truth. They may include stale records,
shared infrastructure, or inherited services that are not automatically authorized.
.PP
Findings, scores, and recommendations help operators prioritize review, but they do not
prove exploitability, ownership, or business impact on their own.
ASRFacet-Rb does not claim stealth, evasion, or guaranteed completeness.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B asrfacet-rb scan example.com --format html --output report.html
Run a full scan and save an HTML report.
.TP
.B asrfacet-rb passive example.com --format json --output passive.json
Run passive discovery only and save JSON output.
.TP
.B asrfacet-rb --web-session
Open the local control panel.
.TP
.B asrfacet-rb --version
Print the installed version.
.TP
.B man asrfrb
Open the alias manual page.
.SH SAFETY
Only use ASRFacet-Rb on systems you own or have explicit written permission to test.
Use scope controls and exclusions to keep the target boundary explicit.
